# bamc
We consider the equilibrium equations of a conducting rod in a uniform magnetic field, motivated by the problem of elctrodynamic tethers. The equations sit in a hierarchy of non-canonical Hamiltonian systems and are integrable if the rod is transversely isotropic, giving a physical realisation to a previously proposed abstract system. The integrals are used to reduce the problem to a four-dimensional canonical system, allowing the geometry of the phase space to be investigated through Poincare sections. When the rod is initially aligned with the magnetic field the system is superintegrable: the phase space breaks down into periodic orbits, corresponding to helical configurations of the rod. --&gt;</description></item><item><title>The buckling of magneto-strictive Cosserat rods</title><link>https://djps.github.io/publications/sinden2011bmc/</link><pubDate>Mon, 25 Jul 2011 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://djps.github.io/publications/sinden2011bmc/</guid><description/></item><item><title>Localisation of a twisted conducting rod in a uniform magnetic field: the Hamiltonian-Hopf-Hopf bifurcation</title><link>https://djps.github.io/publications/vanderheijden2011ltc/</link><pubDate>Mon, 20 Jun 2011 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://djps.github.io/publications/vanderheijden2011ltc/</guid><description/></item><item><title>Integrability, Localisation and Bifurcation of an Elastic Conducting Rod in a Uniform Magnetic Field</title><link>https://djps.github.io/publications/thesis/</link><pubDate>Sat, 20 Jun 2009 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://djps.github.io/publications/thesis/</guid><description/></item><item><title>Spatial chaos of an extensible conducting rod in a uniform magnetic field</title><link>https://djps.github.io/publications/sinden2009sce/</link><pubDate>Sat, 20 Jun 2009 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://djps.github.io/publications/sinden2009sce/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;A preprint can be found on the
